## Loading required package: viridisLite
transactions=read_csv("transactions.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   id = col_double(),
##   account_id = col_double(),
##   date = col_date(format = ""),
##   type = col_character(),
##   amount = col_double(),
##   balance = col_double(),
##   bank = col_character(),
##   account = col_double(),
##   method = col_character(),
##   category = col_character()
## )
tran.count<-transactions %>%
  group_by(account_id=factor(account_id)) %>%
  summarise(N=n())
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
tt = transactions[transactions$account_id == tran.count[which(tran.count$N == max(tran.count$N)),]$account_id,]
#account 8261 with 675 rows of transactions

tt.c=tt[tt$type=="credit",]
tt.d=tt[tt$type=="debit",]
ggplot()+geom_line(data=tt.c,aes(x=date,y=amount,color=type,fill=type),size=1)+geom_line(data=tt.d,aes(x=date,y=amount,color=type,fill=type),size=1)+
  labs(title = "Time series plot of different types") +
  xlab("date") +
  ylab("amount")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text (hjust = 0.5),
        axis.text.x = element_text(hjust=1))
